--> Constructors are the special member functions that are used to initailize the objects
--> It has the same name as that of a clpass
--> Constructors do not have a return type, not even void
--> They're always declared in the public section of the class
--> If we have not created a constructor, the compiler will create a default constructor for us, which will initialize all the data members to some garbage value in case of non-primitive data types value
--> We can have multiple constructors in a class, which is called constructor overloading
    Types of constructora:
        -> Default Constructor  (with no arguments)
        -> Parameterized Constructor (with arguments)
        -> Copy Constructor (Copy of the object as an argument)

    Default Constructor: 
        -> it is the one which contains no argument
        -> it is automatically created if we do not created whe we do not create it 
        
    Parameterized Constructor: 
        -> these are the ones which contains a list of parameters or arguments 
        -> these arguments are used to initialize the data members of the class

    Copy Constructor:
        -> these are the ones which takes reference of another object as a parameter.
        -> in this the values of one object is entirely copied to another object.
        